-- BHP Billiton shares fall 2 percent after Petrohawk deal
-- 
-- Fri Jul 15, 2011 8:00am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/15/us-bhp-idUSTRE76E01E20110715

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - Shares of mining and oil company BHP Billiton fell 2 percent in early trade after the company unveiled a $12.1 billion agreed takeover of U.S. gas producer Petrohawk Energy Corp. 

 At 0005 GMT, BHP shares were down 1.97 percent at A$42.76, underperforming a 0.4 percent fall in the broader market. (Reporting by  Balazs Koranyi )